Also, sometime back a law was passed that gas comapanies don't have to  advertise the ethanol content in their gasolines.  Ethanol burns  hotter than gasoline.  Racetrack down here is known for selling  high ethanol content gas and I've known mechanics who tell their  customers to never run Racetrack gasoline.  Don't know if it's  true but it makes sense.  Cheers...KR

